text: I fixed the summary.  Picking up immediately after the events in Resident Evil: Retribution, the Resident Evil franchise is on its last legs. As the only survivor of what was meant to be humanity's final stand against the undead hordes, "Resident Evil: The Final Chapter" must return to where the nightmare began - Raccoon City, where the Umbrella Corporation is gathering its forces for a final strike against the only remaining survivors of the apocalypse. In a race against time "Resident Evil: The Final Chapter" will join forces with old friends, and an unlikely ally, in an action packed battle with undead hordes and new mutant monsters. Between regaining its superhuman abilities at Wesker's hand and Umbrella's impending attack, this will be "Resident Evil: The Final Chapter"'s most difficult adventure as it fights to save the Resident Evil franchise, which is on the brink of oblivion.

text: Hi all, I am a big fan of RE series both movies n games. This part excite me the most after what I have seen in 1st part. I see every RE movie in theatre with my Mom and she likes to watch all courageous stunts being performed by Milla.   Many times movies dont succeed or generate revenues. RE has big fan following I am sure. For my entire family, RE movies are beyond criticism or rating. We treat these as complete package for family entertainment. Moreover, Milla resides in every single lady today who inspires them to be courageous.   All people should salute Milla for an inspiring essence that she has been giving since release of RE's first installment. We should respect the hidden msg. and morale that we get from movie. RE is beyond comparison. I wish this year's Oscar Academy Award goes to her and Paul for their efforts.   Despite of fact that, RE is an action packed, horror movie I get positive fighting spirit from it especially, Milla's never give up attitude while facing different challenges, situations and phases of life.  I wish that, I personally meet her to thank her and Paul for their never ending efforts and I also look forward to have chains of movies in RE series. If I can participate, act, play or contribute for this I'll be highly obliged.   May Milla win Oscar Academy Award this year. :)

text: The resident evil movies are a great analogy for how Resident Evil video games have become. The first movie, while far from perfect, focused on the survival horror aspect, anyone can die and ammo was limited.  The next few movies Alice slowly became more and more overpowered while the film compensated the lack of actual claustrophobia with explosions, jumpscares and infinite ammo.   Similarly Resident evil 5 and 6 are extremely guilty of this by over relying on their more cinematic cutscenes.
